description.description_en: Stems unbranched or with 2-3 branches per node, 20-160 cm tall, 1-7 mm in diameter; stomata in 1-3 lines in the grooves.sheaths longer than wide, the lower sheaths with a brown band, the upper ones green; teeth 3-9 mm long, having brown centers with white margins, when broken off, leaving a brown rim at top of sheaths. Strobili apiculate.Cross section of stem showing vallecular collenchyma not extending to vallecular canal; endodermis double, i.e. with an inner and outer endodermis.
